  <div class="row">
    <div class="small-12 columns">

      <h2>About</h2>

      <p>The spins began in 2011 as abstract circular oil paintings on acrylic and glass discs and since then have developed through a series of studies involving a variety of media and contexts. Their abstract yet painterly nature serves as an ideal petri dish for wide ranging examinations into the perception and effects of art.</p>

      <ul class="nodecoration">
        <li><a href="#imagereactionstudies">Image Reaction Studies</a></li>
        <li><a href="#placereactionstudies">Place Reaction Studies</a></li>
        <li><a href="#tastestudies">Taste Studies</a></li>
      </ul>

      <p>For information on obtaining a spin study piece, see <a href="{{ root_path }}acquire.html">acquiring works</a>.</p>

    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row">
    <div class="small-12 columns">
      <h2 id="imagereactionstudies">Image Reaction Studies</h2>
      <p>The studies examine how overlaying abstract geometric spins over pre-existing images can imbue the spins with meaning and even purpose, thereby affecting the mood of the underlying image.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

